# On-call runbook — {{projectName}}

> **Owner**: SRE / DevOps. Any engineer should be able to follow this during an on-call rotation.

## Before your shift

- [ ] Read `.agent/reports/heartbeat.md` for known blockers
- [ ] Confirm alert routing reaches you (pager, Slack, email)
- [ ] Know how to access logs/metrics for {{backendStack}}

## Severity guide

| Level | Examples | Response |
|-------|----------|----------|
| SEV1 | Outage, data loss risk | Page CEO + Manager; start `incident.md` |
| SEV2 | Degraded service | Mitigate within 1h; update heartbeat |
| SEV3 | Non-urgent defect | Route to backlog via PO |

## First 15 minutes (any alert)

1. Acknowledge the alert
2. Check recent deploys and error dashboards
3. Write status to `.agent/status/<your-agent>.md`
4. If customer-impacting: follow `docs/runbooks/incident.md`

## Handoff

Append to `.agent/messages/manager.md`:

```markdown
---
from: <your-agent-file>
to: manager
date: <ISO-8601>
subject: On-call handoff
---

- Open incidents:
- Watch items:
- Recent deploys:
```
